  			<h2><a href="http://www.criterion.com/library/expanded_view?f=1&amp;s=release_date">May Titles!</a></h2>
  			<p>Bette Midler lights up the stage in <i>The Rose,</i> headlining a selection of dazzling dramas this May, which also includes Chaplin’s <i>Limelight,</i> Fassbinder’s <i>The Merchant of Four Seasons,</i> and two by Costa-Gavras: <i>The Confession</i> and <i>State of Siege.</i> Plus, <i>Make Way for Tomorrow</i> on Blu.</p>
  			<a href="http://www.criterion.com/library/expanded_view?f=1&amp;s=release_date" class="readmore" title="Read more">Learn more</a>
  			<a href="http://www.criterion.com/library/expanded_view?f=1&amp;s=release_date" class="spotlight_link">&nbsp;</a>
  		</li>
  		<li class="slide3">
  			<h6>Spotlight</h6>
  			<h2><a href="http://www.criterion.com/current/posts/3461-mirrors-of-bergman">Mirrors of Bergman</a></h2>
  			<p>From <i>Port of Call</i> to <i>Persona</i> to <i>Autumn Sonata,</i> :: kogonada finds evidence of Ingmar Bergman’s preoccupation with women examining their reflections, in this poetic new video essay.</p>
  			<a href="http://www.criterion.com/current/posts/3461-mirrors-of-bergman" class="readmore" title="Read more">Watch video</a>
  			<a href="http://www.criterion.com/current/posts/3461-mirrors-of-bergman" class="spotlight_link">&nbsp;</a>
  		</li>
  		<li class="slide4">
  			<h6>Spotlight</h6>
  			<h2><a href="http://www.criterion.com/films/28072-a-day-in-the-country">Jean Renoir Goes Boating</a></h2>
  			<p>The illustrious French director’s long unavailable <i>A Day in the Country,</i> a comic and poignant vignette about city folk on a weekend jaunt, is finally on <span class="caps">DVD</span> and Blu-ray.</p>
  			<a href="http://www.criterion.com/films/28072-a-day-in-the-country" class="readmore" title="Read more">Learn more</a>
  			<a href="http://www.criterion.com/films/28072-a-day-in-the-country" class="spotlight_link">&nbsp;</a>
  		</li>
	</ul>
	<ul class="spotlight_right">
	    <li><a href="http://www.criterion.com/films/784-an-autumn-afternoon"><img alt="Autumn_spot_large" height="385" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/criterion-production/spotlights/1249-6a8b3c478802f9f974cdb585fad740e9/autumn_spot_large.jpg" width="602" /></a></li>
	    <li><a href="http://www.criterion.com/library/expanded_view?f=1&amp;s=release_date"><img alt="Rose_spot_large" height="385" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/criterion-production/spotlights/1248-ba0b434d773cce0a73697f43d5729b38/rose_spot_large.jpg" width="602" /></a></li>
	    <li><a href="http://www.criterion.com/current/posts/3461-mirrors-of-bergman"><img alt="Mirrors_spot_large" height="385" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/criterion-production/spotlights/1247-b70fa23b4d6c88abdd6646210e841141/mirrors_spot_large.jpg" width="602" /></a></li>
	    <li><a href="http://www.criterion.com/films/28072-a-day-in-the-country"><img alt="Day_country_spot_large" height="385" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/criterion-production/spotlights/1246-a17db9ff2de21e11b3847824ddb10c25/day_country_spot_large.jpg" width="602" /></a></li>
