</a>
        <h4>
          <a href="/current/posts/667-an-autumn-afternoon-a-fond-farewell"><i>An Autumn Afternoon:</i> A Fond Farewell</a>
        </h4>

        <p>
            By <strong>Geoff Andrew</strong>
            &bull;
          17 February 2015
          &bull;
          <a href="/current/posts/667-an-autumn-afternoon-a-fond-farewell#comments">1 comment</a>
          <br />
          Yasujiro Ozu’s final film is a visually clever domestic drama whose emotional complexities linger in the mind.
          <a href="/current/posts/667-an-autumn-afternoon-a-fond-farewell" title="Read more">Read more »</a>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
          <a href="/current/posts/3460-don-t-look-now-seeing-red">
            
<img alt="Dontlooknow_red_thumbnail" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/criterion-production/images/5422-19d13a0657c7399041fe8e46b6b1cc72/dontlooknow_red_thumbnail.jpg" />
</a>
        <h4>
          <a href="/current/posts/3460-don-t-look-now-seeing-red"><i>Don’t Look Now:</i> Seeing Red</a>
        </h4>

        <p>
            By <strong>David Thompson</strong>
            &bull;
          12 February 2015
          &bull;
          <a href="/current/posts/3460-don-t-look-now-seeing-red#comments">0 comments</a>
          <br />
          With its provocative ambiguities, tender compassion, and fragmented editing style, this supernatural classic is a pure dose of Nicolas Roeg.
          <a href="/current/posts/3460-don-t-look-now-seeing-red" title="Read more">Read more »</a>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
          <a href="/current/posts/3459-a-day-in-the-country-jean-renoir-s-sunday-outing">
            
<img alt="Country1_thumbnail" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/criterion-production/images/5421-4d3f72d51c3d48fb28135cfa418e2aa5/country1_thumbnail.jpg" />
</a>
        <h4>
          <a href="/current/posts/3459-a-day-in-the-country-jean-renoir-s-sunday-outing"><i>A Day in the Country:</i> Jean Renoir’s Sunday Outing</a>
        </h4>

        <p>
            By <strong>Gilberto Perez</strong>
            &bull;
          11 February 2015
          &bull;
          <a href="/current/posts/3459-a-day-in-the-country-jean-renoir-s-sunday-outing#comments">1 comment</a>
          <br />
          The late film scholar beautifully analyzes the visual lyricism of the French master’s legendary short work.
          <a href="/current/posts/3459-a-day-in-the-country-jean-renoir-s-sunday-outing" title="Read more">Read more »</a>
        </p>
      </li>
  </ul>
</div>

  
